					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">...and to be totally clear, it's not a convention or choice for the individual programmer - the assembler will assemble the instruction into different opcodes based on whether or not there's a '#' to indicate the immediate addressing mode.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

